cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY

The paper describes the evolution of controllers for a simulated car racing task using neural networks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Additionally, the use of controllers based on force fields and action sequences suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The fact that the controllers are for a robotic task also suggests that it may belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the use of egocentric and Newtonian inputs suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
